1. icons
  react-icons
  npm install --save react-icons
  It has different font packages
  Ex: for Font Awesome Icon
    import {ICON_NAME} from 'react-icons/fa';
  Ex: for Material Design Icon  
    import {ICON_NAME} from 'react-icons/md';
  
  Props: color, size
  Ex: <FaReact color='purple' size='10rem' />

  If we want to maintain thru' the application, the same color & size of the icons
  Instead of specifying individually, we can use 'icon context provider' that the library offers.

  import { IconContext } from 'react-icons';
  then wrap the top level component with the context provider &
  for the value specify an object (which will have corresponding props)

  NOTE: individual props values provided to component will have precedence over the context value
